d 'DPATH': Decision-Path Construction and Infrastructure Auditing
d
d dpath implements the decision infrastructure paradigm (Hait, 2025)
d for analysing AI-mediated institutional decision processes in
d longitudinal panel data. It treats decision sequences as the
d primary unit of analysis and provides five core subcommands:
d build (construct path object), describe (path descriptors),
d dri (Decision Reliability Index following Cronbach, 1951),
d entropy (Shannon path entropy, Shannon 1948),
d equity (group disparity diagnostics), and audit (full pipeline).
d
d KW: decision paths
d KW: longitudinal
d KW: panel data
d KW: institutional AI
d KW: reliability
d KW: entropy
d KW: equity
d
d Requires: Stata version 15
d
d Author: Subir Hait, Michigan State University
d Support: haitsubi@msu.edu
d
d Distribution-Date: 20250309
d
f dpath.ado
f dpath.sthlp
f dpath_example.do
